AB  - Alternative methods of computing estimates of inequality measures from grouped data are critically examined in terms of their theoretical and empirical properties. The use of a simple “split-histogram” technique of interpolation is explained and supported. Theoretical and empirical support is also provided for the “⅓/⅔ rule”—a simple computational procedure for a point estimate of an inequality measure derived from its standard grouping bounds.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
